name: Ae Vang
specialty: Ae works with English and Hmong speaking children, adolescents and adults in individual and family therapy. Her experience includes working with stress, depression, anxiety, difficult life changes, relationship difficulties, trauma, and abuse. Ae utilizes an eclectic approach to therapy.

name: Alison Yang
specialty: Therapy for individuals, couples, families, teens, and children. Offer play therapy.

name: Amanda Moua
specialty: Amanda works with children and adults of all ages, primarily in individual and family therapy. She enjoys working with children who are experiencing social, emotional and behavioral problems in school, home and environment. She also has experience working with individuals who are dealing with depression, stress, anxiety, family conflict, life transitions, trauma and abuse or neglect. Amanda utilizes strengths based and relationship based therapies to assist and support clients in working through stressors and barriers. Amanda is able to provide therapy in both English and Hmong.

name: Bea Vue-Benson
specialty: I believe in treating the person as a whole. Who you are as an emotional, mental, physical, and spiritual being is important to our work together. I take seriously your culture, gender, environment, sexual orientation, family systems, and personal experiences. Your health and wellness are intrinsically linked to these factors.
